xf86-video-crime - Xorg driver for the SGI O2 CRIME rendering engine
====================================================================

An Xorg driver for the CRIME rendering engine found in SGI O2
workstations, based on the NetBSD xsrc driver by Michael Lorenz,
repackaged with modern autotools and ported to the current
xorg-server API.

All rendering goes through the CRIME engine: the visible framebuffer
is tiled and not usefully CPU addressable, so the driver keeps a
malloc'ed shadow for fb fallbacks and transfers pixels with the XAA
ImageWrite/ReadPixmap hooks.  An X server with XAA support is
therefore required.

Backends
--------

* NetBSD/OpenBSD (wscons): the classic behaviour - the wsdisplay
  device (default /dev/ttyE0) provides mode switching, colormap,
  blanking and the hardware cursor, and the engine is mapped through
  the wsdisplay mmap interface.

* Linux (gbefb): the framebuffer console device (default /dev/fb0,
  driver "SGI GBE") provides the display information, colormap and
  blanking; the CRIME engine at physical 0x15000000 and the GBE
  display backend at 0x16000000 are mapped through /dev/mem.  The
  32x32 GBE hardware cursor is programmed directly through the
  CRMFB cursor registers.

The device can be overridden with Option "device" in the Device
section, or the XDEVICE environment variable.

Building
--------

  ./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr
  make
  make install
